{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place chives in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add roast beef and chop <b>20 sec\/\/speed 4<b>.","Add roast potatoes, roast vegetables, creamed horseradish, salt and pepper then mix <b>15-20 sec\/\/speed 4<b> until combined. Divide into 8 equal-sized balls (approx. 75 g each), press to compact mixture then shape each into a round patty. Place on a tray in fridge for 20 minutes to firm up.","After this time, heat 1 tsp oil in a frying pan over a medium-high heat and fry patties in batches until golden on both sides and hot in the centre (3-5 minutes each side). Set aside and cover to keep warm.","Heat remaining 1 tsp oil in frying pan then fry eggs until cooked as desired, seasoning with salt and pepper to taste. Serve patties hot with fried egg and a green salad."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["10 fresh chives, cut in pieces (4 cm)","200 g leftover roast beef, cut in pieces","200 g leftover roast potatoes","200 g leftover roast vegetables","1 Tbsp creamed horseradish","1 tsp fine sea salt, plus extra to taste","1 - 2 pinches ground black pepper, to taste","2 tsp olive oil, for frying","4 eggs, medium or large","salad, for serving"]}],"id":"r376583","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-_mXsoBWRTqY\/XZQFjnshUhI\/AAAAAAAAb0I\/1Nnk3nAg0fMqdz9ZbDX5aVNfvYjWfbIZACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_6wSPUTOyhx5Xb20R.png","title":"Leftover Roast Patties with Egg","publishedAt":"2018-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"23 g","fat":"23 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"15 g","calories":"1517 kJ \/ 364 kcal"},"usefulItems":"frying pan, fish slice, tray, hob, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Also works well served with a poached egg.","Substitute leftover roast beef with leftover roast lamb. Substitute creamed horseradish with mustard, to taste."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","45m","4 portions"]}